x4freetext: -THE RESONANCE INTEGRALS OF CU-63,CU-65,AG-107,TB-159,
DY-164 AND HO-165.
VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR.
WITH A 100 MICRO AMPERE MAGNETICALLY
ANALYSED BEAM OF 3 MEV DEUTERONS FROM THE VAN DE
GRAAFF ACCELERATOR STRIKING A THICK BERYLLIUM METAL
TARGET.
.TABLE 3 IN JP/A,7,2318 GIVES THE FOIL THICKNESS OF
DIFFERENT MATERIALS UNDER INVESTIGATION.
A SIMPLE ACTIVATION TECHNIQUE EMPLOYING
CADMIUM RATIO MEASUREMENTS WAS USED,WHERE RESONANCE
INTEGRALS ARE MEASURED IN A SLOWING DOWN FLUX WHICH
IS CLOSELY PROPORTIONAL TO 1/E (E IS NEUTRON ENERGY)
RELATIVE TO TWO SELECTED STANDARD MATERIALS,MANGANESE
AND GOLD,WHOSE RESONANCE INTEGRALS ARE ACCURATE TO
ABOUT 4 PERCENT.
A FISSION CHAMBER AND A BORON-COATED
IONIZATION CHAMBER WERE USED FOR MONITORING THE
THERMALIZED NEUTRON FLUX DENSITY.
THE ACTIVATED FOILS WERE ASSAYED IN A 4 PI
BETA GAS FLOW PROPORTIONAL COUNTER.
.FOLLOWING INFORMATION GIVEN IN JP/A,7,2318
.THICKNESS AND COMPOSITION OF FOILS.
.PRODUCT HALF-LIFE.
.THE TRANSMISSION OF RESONANCE NEUTRONS THOUGH THE
CADMIUM COVERS.
.THE WESTCOTT FACTOR WHICH ACCOUNTS FOR THE DEVIATION
OF THE CROSS SECTION FROM A 1/V BEHAVIOR IN THE
THERMAL REGION.
.THE SMALL CORRECTION TERM OF WALKER ET AL.WHICH
ACCOUNTS FOR THAT PART OF A LOW-LYING RESONANCE WHICH
LIES BELOWS THE EFFECTIVE CADMIUM CUT-OFF ENERGY.
.TABLE 2 GIVES THE PERCENTAGES UNCERTAINTIES IN THE
2200 M/SEC NEUTRON CAPTURE CROSS SECTION FOR TB-159
AND HO-165.
.TABLE 3 GIVES THE RESONANCE SELF-SHIELDING FACTORS
FOR THE FOILS FOR DIFFERENT MATERIALS CONSIDERED.
.TABLE 4 GIVES THE RESONANCE INTEGRAL RESULTS.
.TABLE 5 GIVES THE PERCENTAGE UNCERTAINTIES IN THE
RESONANCE INTEGRALS.
.TABLE 6 GIVES THE COEFFICIENTS FOR COMPUTING THE
CHANGE IN THE REDUCED RESONANCE INTEGRAL DUE TO
CHANGE IN THE REDUCED RESONANCE INTEGRAL OF GOLD AND
MANGANESE.
.RESONANCE INTEGRAL VALUES GIVEN HERE ARE THE REDUCED
RESONANCE INTEGRAL VALUES.
.VALUES FROM (JP/A,07,2318,74  )
.CORRECTIONS FOR DEAD-TIME AND BACKGROUND.
.THE SYSTEMATIC UNCERTAINTIES WERE ESTIMATED TO BE
NEGLIGIBLE COMPARED WITH THE RANDOM UNCERTAINTIES.
.THE ACTIVATED HO FOILS WERE CHECKED CARREFULLY FOR
ANY IMPURITIES BY GAMMA-RAY SPECTROSCOPY AND NO
CONTAMINATION WAS OBSERVED.
.THE RANDOM UNCERTAINTIES AT A 99 PERCENT CONFIDENCE
LEVEL WERE ESTIMATED FROM THE DISPERSION OF THE
MEASUREMENTS,AND INCLUDE THE STATISTICAL COUNTING
UNCERTAINTIES IN THE THREE CADMIUM RATIOS PER
MEASUREMENT,TOGETHER WITH UNCERTAINTIES IN THE
RELATIVE BETA EFFICIENCIES AND MASSES OF THE FOILS
PAIRS.
.THE GREATEST SYSTEMATIC UNCERTAINTY DUE TO THE
REFERENCE STANDARDS AU AND MN DEPENDS MOSTLY ON THE
MAGNITUDES OF THE CADMIUM RATIOS.
